<HEADLINE> 2 Engineers of Iranian Firm Killed in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Two engineers working on the
Clifton Bridge in Pakistan's southern port city of Karachi were
killed Saturday afternoon when unidentified gunmen opened fire at
them.
</P>
<P>
According to an initial police report, the assailants had come
in a taxi and a motorcycle.
</P>
<P>
The two engineers got seriously injured as a result of firing
and were rushed to a nearby hospital and died later.
</P>
<P>
Further details of the incident were still unknown. 
</P>
