<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Thailand Wish to Boost Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 21 (Xinhua) --Senior officials of Vietnam and
Thailand expressed confidence Saturday that Southeast Asia would
continue being the most dynamic region in the world once the
financial crisis ends.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Nguyen
Manh Cam Saturday met with visiting Thai Prime Minister Office
Director Somboon Rahong in Hanoi.
</P>
<P>
According to Vietnam News Agency (VNA), Rahong said, "The thai
business people always consider Vietnam a reliable and attractive
investment venue."
</P>
<P>
He said political stability, timely adjustment of the
government, and qualification of the workforce in Vietnam
attracted Thai investors.
</P>
<P>
The Thai official admitted that the current financial crisis
produced adverse impacts on Thailand's investment in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that members of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) would strengthen solidarity to solve the aftermath
caused by the current regional financial crisis, and make hostile
schemes designed by outside forces null and void.
</P>
<P>
The two countries should strive to boost bilateral ties to
become a good model for other members of ASEAN, he added.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Manh Cam expressed his deep sympathy to the Thai
government and people's difficulties caused by the financial
crisis and hoped that Thailand and other regional countries would
soon get rid of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister affirmed the Thai official that
Vietnam always pursues a foreign policy of independence and
sovereignty. Cooperation should be boosted on the principle of
respecting each other's national sovereignty and free from
outside imposition, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Cam said more than ever before, it is now time for ASEAN
countries to enhance mutual solidarity, cooperation and assistance
for development since a prosperous nation will add strength to its
region, and a prosperous region will add strength to the world.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Thailand share great potential to accelerate their
comprehensive cooperation in the interest of each nation and for
stability and development in the region, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
