<HEADLINE> Japan to Help Russia Enter World Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Japan is interested in
promoting Russia's economic reforms and ready to help Russia enter
the world economic system, in particular the APEC and the WTO, the
Japanese embassy in Moscow has said in a report.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax received Saturday the report dealing with the
implementation of the Hashimoto-Yeltsin plan developed at the
informal summit in Krasnoyarsk last November.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, in order to promote Russia's admission
to the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation organization (APEC)
Russian experts dealing with APEC matters will be invited to Japan
in March.
</P>
<P>
In the near future, full-scale bilateral talks on admission to
the World Trade Organization (WTO) are expected to be held.
Besides, Japan is considering to offer further technical
assistance in the matter.
</P>
<P>
As for the Russian reforms, Japan will continue steps launched
in November 1997 to cushion the terms of foreign trade insurance
in Russia. For instance, it plans to significantly reduce
insurance rates for Russia, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The embassy report also said that Tokyo is drafting an
agreement on the protection of Japanese investments in Russia. The
first round of talks on such an agreement was held in
mid-February.
</P>
<P>
It said last December investment contracts totaling 3.39
million U.S. dollars were signed on three projects involving small
and medium-sized companies in the Russian Far East and Eastern
Siberia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
