<DOCNO> XIE19980222.0028 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liberian President Amends Relations with ECOMOG </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Liberian President Charles
Taylor is trying to amend relations with the west African
peacekeeping force (ECOMOG), which has helped end his country's
seven-year civil war and ousted the military junta in neighboring
Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
A week ago, Liberia has recalled its ambassador to Nigeria in
protest over ECOMOG's arrest of 25 senior junta officials
arriving in Liberia in a helicopter.
</P>
<P>
The Liberian government regarded it as a violation of its
sovereignty and demanded ECOMOG hand over the helicopter and
junta officials.
</P>
<P>
The action has led to speculations that other junta leaders
still at large might seek refuge in Liberia.
</P>
<P>
However, according to a statement of the ECOMOG high command
based in the capital Monrovia, Taylor has assured that the
Liberian government will arrest the junta leader Johnny Paul
Koroma if he enters Liberia.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued on Friday quoted Taylor as saying that
the decision was necessary because "Liberia is a member of ECOWAS
(Economic Community of West African States), which is working to
ensure that peace returns in Sierra Leone".
</P>
<P>
This is the latest official position of the Liberian
government on the Sierra Leonean crisis since it complained
ECOMOG's arrest of the fleeing junta officials.
</P>
<P>
According to the British Broadcasting Corporation Saturday,
Taylor has held talks with ECOMOG force Commander Timothy Shelpidi
on bilateral relations and the
development in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting held over the weekend, Taylor impressed
upon ECOMOG the urgent need to screen thousands of Sierra Leonean
refugees streaming into northern Liberia daily.
</P>
<P>
He then sent an appeal to the United Nations and the
international community to rush to the aid of the more than
100,000 Sierra Leoneans who entered northern Liberia as a result
of the latest military situation.
</P>
<P>
The refugees are in dire need of food and safe drinking water,
Taylor said.
</P>
<P>
Taylor also called on the ECOMOG high command to bridge the
communication gap between the Liberian authorities and the
peacekeeping force.
</P>
<P>
The Liberian government has had friction with ECOMOG for some
time.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, it had opposed to ECOMOG's use of its territory to
launch attack on the military junta in Sierra Leone and asked the
peacekeeping force to leave Liberia.
</P>
<P>
It is also against the planned ECOMOG involvement in the
restructuring and training of the country's post-war army.
</P>
<P>
Taylor has also been accused of sending his former warring factional
fighters to help the junta in its fight against ECOMOG. 
</P>
</TEXT>
