<HEADLINE> Pak Supports Diplomatic Solution of Iraqi Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
wrote a letter Saturday to U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan,
reiterating Pakistan's support for a diplomatic solution of the
Iraqi crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to a spokesman from the Foreign Ministry, Pakistan is
constantly monitoring the situation in the Gulf. Pakistan's
position on the Iraqi standoff is in accordance with the
principles of the U.N. Charter.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Prime Minister Sharif conveyed concern
at the escalating tension in the Gulf in his letter to Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
Sharif also underscored the peaceful resolution of disputes as
the cardinal principle of Pakistan's foreign policy, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
In his letter, the prime minister has called for the full
implementation of all U.N. resolutions whether they pertain to
Iraq, Kashmir or Palestine.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan believes that it is through the observance of the U.N.
Security Council Resolutions that the current tension in the Gulf
region can be defused, the letter said.
</P>
<P>
The letter stated that Pakistan upholds the sovereignty and
territorial integrity of all countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister has also expressed concern that the use of
force in the current crisis will result in the sufferings of the
innocent civilians in the Gulf countries.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan is particularly worried about the well being of
several hundred thousands Pakistan nationals in the region. Their
safety is of prime importance to Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
