<HEADLINE> China Unicom to Expand GSM Digital Cellular Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The Zhejiang branch of China
Unicom, the country's second-largest state telecommunications
operator, has signed a contract with Canada's Northern Telecom Ltd
(Nortel) for the expansion of the GSM digital cellular phone
network.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with China Unicom, the expansion,
slated to be completed in mid-1998, will increase the capacity of
Zhejiang's GSM network to 130,000 subscribers.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, worth 27 million U.S. dollars,
Nortel will provide digital switching and radio equipment,
including the latest range of Base Transceiver Stations (BTS). The
project will enable Zhejiang Unicom to expand its coverage in
Hangzhou and Wenzhou cities, and bring Shaoxing City within its
sphere of operations.
</P>
<P>
China Unicom is the only telecom service provider other than
China Telecom run by the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
