<HEADLINE> Chinese Doctors Remove Large Tumor from Cervical Vertebra </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Doctors here have removed a
giant tumor from the cervical vertebra of a young patient, the
first successful surgical endeavor of its kind by Chinese medical
workers.
</P>
<P>
After a five-hour operation, Hou Jinsheng, a senior orthopedist
at Shanghai's Changhai Hospital, and his team managed to remove
the egg-sized tumor from a 16-year-old middle-school student
surnamed Guo. Guo left the hospital two weeks after the operation.
</P>
<P>
In addition, medical experts in the city have removed
gallstones from 20 patients using dilators with mirrors.
</P>
