<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Province Opens Wider to Outside World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi
Province has made great progress in increasing cooperation and
exchanges with the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The province has kept a favorable balance of foreign trade for
several years, growing by four percent annually. Local exports
rose to 1.3 billion US dollars-worth in 1997 from less than 1.1
billion US dollars in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi exports nearly 10,000 varieties of products to more
than 130 countries and regions. Exports of high-value-added and
hi-tech products, mainly machinery, electronic, light industrial
and textile goods, have been increasing remarkably.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the province has been going all-out to attract
overseas investment. During the 1993-1997 period it used 2.1
billion US dollars of such investment.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the transfer of shares and managerial rights, and
auction activities have been brisk.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors are becoming keen on funding local
infrastructure construction projects, especially in the fields of
petroleum, power and coal, and the development of local resources.
</P>
<P>
So far, the province has established friendly relations with 30
overseas cities. Over the past five years nearly 2.4 million
overseas tourists have visited Shaanxi, bringing in 750 million
US dollars-worth of foreign exchange.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
