<DOCNO> XIE19980222.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cayard on Course for Record Win in Yachting Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Swedish entry EF Language,
skippered by American Paul Cayard, on Sunday had just over 500
miles to go to finish leg five in the Whitbread Round the World
Race.
</P>
<P>
While still on track to win by a record margin, the advantage
has dropped from the 600 plus miles anticipated two days ago.
</P>
<P>
Cayard and his crew now led second-placed Brunel Sunergy by 464
miles, and were travelling at a close speed.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch entry skippered by Roy Heiner, still had a 46-mile
advantage over third-placed Chessie Racing.
</P>
<P>
Heiner and his crew were smelling their first whiff of success
after finishing last or next to last on all previous legs of the
race, and would fight to defend their positions all the way to the
finish. 
</P>
</TEXT>
