<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen to Improve Environmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 22 (Xinhua) -- This Special Economic Zone,
located just to the north of Hong Kong, plans to invest 8.6
billion yuan (about one billion US dollars) in environmental
protection projects.
</P>
<P>
"Shenzhen will phase in an environmental protection program
over the next eight years," said Li Zhibin, mayor of the city,
adding that much attention has been paid to the city's environment
as its economy develops rapidly.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen was cited by the central government for its
environmental protection efforts and selected as one of the
top five cities with model urban environments last year.
</P>
<P>
The city government has decided to increase its financial input
in environmental protection to more than two percent of its
gross domestic product from this year.
</P>
<P>
The mid- and long-term program for environmental protection
involves water pollution treatment, garbage treatment and land
erosion control.
</P>
<P>
About four billion yuan will be spent on water pollution
treatment, and a land area of 147 sq km vulnerable to erosion will
be brought under control.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to keeping waste water from polluting
the Shenzhen reservoir. The project will treat waste water in an
area of 60.5 sq km around the reservoir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
