<HEADLINE> Books Published to Commemorate Zhou Enlai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Two collections of articles
written by the late Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai have been published
to mark the 100th anniversary of the birth of the great statesman.
</P>
<P>
Zhou was born on March 5, 1898 in Huai'an County, east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
One book contains essays written by Zhou during his middle
school years in Tianjin, 1914-1917.
</P>
<P>
"Zhou Enlai's Japan Journal", containing examples of his
original handwriting, gives insights into Zhou's experiences and
thoughts during his one-year sojourn in Japan in 1918.
</P>
<P>
The compilation was done by experts with the Party Literature
Research Center of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China and the Museum of the Chinese Revolution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
