<DOCNO> XIE19980222.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> In-Depth Reform Vital to Large Enterprises: State Councilor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The revitalization of large
enterprises must be based on the deepening of reform, scientific
management, a better industrial lineup, advanced science and
talented personnel, according to State Councilor Li Tieying.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the remark Saturday
at a seminar on the successful experience of Jiangsu Province's
Chunlan Group, one of the country's major air-conditioner
producers.
</P>
<P>
Chunlan emerged in the mid-1980s as an amalgamation of three
small factories. At that time it only had fixed assets amounting
to 2.8 million yuan. But by June 1996 the total assets of the
group had reached three billion yuan (about 361 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
This accomplishment is attributed to the in-depth reform of the
company's investment and operation mechanism, Li said, adding that
Chunlan's experience indicates that reform acts as the driving
force behind enterprises and can raise economic returns to a great
extent.
</P>
<P>
He noted that correct strategic decisions are vital to an
enterprise's existence, and strict and scientific management has
played an important role in helping Chunlan reach its goals.
</P>
<P>
In market economy conditions an optimized industrial pattern
and product mix have brought about remarkable returns and rapid
growth in the group, Li said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the emphasis on advanced science and talented
professionals has helped the group reduce costs, raise economic
returns and achieve robust progress, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
