<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-22 13:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq accuses US of threatening Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Iraq Sunday accused the United
States of posing a real threat to stability, security and peace in
the Middle East, the Iraqi News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. tends to interfere in regional affairs and seeks to
control the oil resources in the region, an official spokesman of
the Iraqi Ministry of Culture and Information said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. damages the peace in the Middle East by supporting
Israel's policy of continued occupation of Arab lands, the
spokesman said while commenting on a report broadcast by the
"Voice of America" (VOA) radio Saturday.
</P>
<P>
VOA's report said that there is no bigger threat to the Middle
East security than that posed by the Iraqi government.
</P>
<P>
It is a continuation of "lies made by American President Bill
Clinton and his aides," that the United Nations Special
Commission (UNSCOM) "detected and destroyed Iraq's banned
weapons," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"It is Iraq which destroyed its banned weapons in 1991 and
informed the UNSCOM of that," he said, adding that Iraq then
eliminated the rest in 1994 under the supervision of the UNSCOM.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. commission must verify that Iraq has dismantled all
its weapons of mass destruction before the Security Council will
lift the economic sanctions imposed on Iraq in 1990 after its
invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The UNSCOM has found no banned weapons by itself in Iraq, the
Iraqi spokesman said adding that its discovery of Iraq's banned
weapons has been dependent on Iraq's cooperation and compliance
with the U.N. Resolutions.
</P>
<P>
He accused the U.S. of being the first country to use weapons
of mass destruction against Japanese civilians at the end of the
Second World War, and later against the peoples of Cambodia and
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
It is an illusion of the U.S. that show of military muscle
would intimidate Arabs and Muslims and induce them to kneel down
and accept its aggression on the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has vowed to attack Iraq if it does not grant full and
unfettered access to the U.N. arms inspectors to all sites
suspected of hiding the banned weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
