<HEADLINE> Second-Phase Resettlement Starts at Three Gorges Area of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Hubei Province in central China
has begun a second-phase resettlement project for the construction
of the gigantic Three Gorges Power Project on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
According to a meeting here on the resettlement, in the next
six years, the province will move 71,000 farmers and urbanites as
well as 52 industrial and mining enterprises in the project area
to other places, build a floor space of 2.19 million square
meters, 80 kilometers of roads, and some harbors.
</P>
<P>
The first-phase resettlement project ended last November, when
the Yangtze River at the Three Gorges was dammed.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the second-phase resettlement will be more
difficult than the first-phase project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
