<HEADLINE> Tianjin Zoo Holds Tiger Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The zoo in this north China
port city held a Tiger festival on February 15-22 to make
people more aware of the importance of protecting this endangered
species.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two decades, the zoo has raised about 100 tigers,
most of which have been sent to zoos in other cities in China.
</P>
<P>
The zoon during the festival launched a campaign to spread
knowledge about tigers and invited visitors to watch the feeding of
tigers in the zoo.
</P>
<P>
A beverage company in Beijing has donated money to support one
of the tigers, named "Baobao", for the next two years.
</P>
<P>
The zoo has five Manchurian tigers and one South China tiger,
which it borrowed from the zoo in Chongqing City, Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years people from all walks of life have
donated a total of 1.5 million yuan to the zoo for the upkeep
of endangered species. 
</P>
</TEXT>
