<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Party Official Calls on Provincial Newspapers to Improve Reporting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Ding Guan'gen, member of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China (CPC), today called on newspapers at the provincial level
to focus their work on publicity concerning the resolutions
adopted by the 15th Congress of the CPC held last September.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a four-day conference of leading editors of the
newspapers run by the CPC provincial committees, Ding urged them
to assist the fulfilment of the various strategic tasks set by the
congress.
</P>
<P>
Ding, also head of the Publicity Department of the CPC Central
Committee, said that while keeping the central tasks of the Party
firmly in view, the newspapers should continue to keep to a
consistent course in ideology, politics and action, along the
guidelines laid down by the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin
at its core.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the newspapers should play a positive role in
their supervisory functions so as to improve the Party's work, and
promote the work of reform and opening up, and social stability.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hoped that the newspapers would improve their
reporting of China's economic progress and set aside space for the
people to voice their opinions.
</P>
<P>
He also recommended that they increase the amount of
information that they provide by carrying fewer long stories but
more short stories and on-spot reports.
</P>
<P>
He called on the newspapers to train more capable editors,
reporters and managers so as to meet the demands of the new
situation in the coming years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
