<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Development Zones in Chinese Province Develop Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The development zones in
north China's Hebei Province are developing rapidly.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, 21 development zones had been built in the
province. They had had 2,003 operational enterprises, with another
532 under construction. Last year, the development zones generated
more than 18 billion yuan in industrial and agricultural output
value, 630 million yuan in taxes, and 210 million yuan in foreign
exchanges from exports.
</P>
<P>
The first development zone in the province was set up in
Qinhuangdao in 1984. Of the 21 development zones, 19 are economic
and technological development zones and the rest two are
state-level hi-tech development zones.
</P>
<P>
The zones have introduced distinctive methods involving
infrastructure construction, the use of overseas investment and
the improvement of investment environment, to promote their
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Surrounding the capital of Beijing and the port city of
Tianjin, the province borders on the sea in the east and is one of
the country's traditional industrial bases.  
</P>
</TEXT>
