<HEADLINE> North China Builts Skiing Rink </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The largest skiing rink
in north China has opened to tourists at the Saihanba Forest Park
in Weichang County of Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The skiing rink, covering an area of two million square meters,
is located at the Mulan Hunting Field, which used to be open only
to emperors and royal family members of the Qing Dynasty
(1644-1911).
</P>
<P>
The rink has three 30-meter-wide skiing lanes, one for
beginners, and the other two for skillful skiers.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that the Mulan Hunting Field has the best natural
condition for skiing sports, where snow season starts in October
every year and ends in May next year. The outdoor temperature is
at between 16 to 18 degrees below zero Centigrade in snow season.
</P>
<P>
There, tourists can go skating and hunting, take sledges
moving on the snow field, and enjoy the beautiful landscapes at
the Mulan Hunting Field.  
</P>
</TEXT>
