<HEADLINE> Konadu Retains WBA Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Nana Yaw Konadu of Ghana
knocked out Venezuelan challenger Habran Torres to retain his WBA
bantamweight title at Mar del Plata on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Konadu was on the canvas at the end of the
first round but responded by knocking out Torres with a straight
right at the start of the second.
</P>
<P>
Konadu, who won the champion last June, improved his record to
38 wins, three defeats and one draw. He also held the WBC title
between 1989 and 1991. 
