<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3.2 Million People in Mountainous Area of Anhui Out of Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, February 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 3.2 million poor
people in the mountainous area in east China's Anhui province have
bidden farewell to poverty in the past ten years.
</P>
<P>
The economy in the Dabieshan mountain area in Anhui grew slowly
10 years ago, mainly because of poor transport conditions and
hostile environment. More than half of the seven million people
in the area were living under the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
To help them out of poverty, the local government began to take
measures to tap the abundant resources in the mountain area.
</P>
<P>
In the past 10 years, 71 large bases have been built in the
area to produce local special products such as tea and Chinese
chestnuts. These production bases cover a total of 140,000 ha.
</P>
<P>
Some 150 special markets have also been built to attract
traders across the country. The transaction volume of these
markets has totaled one billion yuan so far.
</P>
<P>
Processing of mountain-based products has also been given green
lights to develop. So far, more than 100 such firms have been set
up.
</P>
<P>
The development of the mountain resources has increased
farmers' income. In 1997, the per-capita income for farmers in the
area reached 1,700 yuan, 260 yuan more than in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The local government has promised to help another 20,000 poor
people shake off poverty this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
