<HEADLINE> Dhaka International Trade Fair Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The month-long fourth Dhaka
International Trade fair (DITF) '98 opened by Bangladeshi Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, the prime minister called the
country's entrepreneurs to be far-sighted, active and industrious
to exert and consolidate the nation's due position in the world
trade.
</P>
<P>
"The whole world is going for economic internationalism, and
Bangladesh has to take careful steps to face the challenges of the
21st century, which would be an age of tough competition in global
business," she said.
</P>
<P>
She expressed her belief that the fair would contribute
considerably to the ample demonstration of Bangladesh's products
as well as to increase fraternity among the participating nations.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair would usher in a new dimension for Bangladesh in
the international trade arena, the prime minister stated.
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the Ministry of Industries and Commerce
and the Export promotion Board, the trade fair occupies a total
area of about 140,000 square meters, with 35 pavilions, 57 mini
pavilions and 272 stalls.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the fair are about 100 companies from foreign
countries including China, Iran, Japan, Singapore, Thailand,
Australia, India, Korea, Britain, Denmark, Italy, Malaysia,
Pakistan and the United States. Besides nearly 300 local firms
including joint venture enterprises.
</P>
<P>
On displaying and for sale at the fair are a variety of
products from the latest model computers to fast food.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh holds trade fair every year since 1995 and local
firms earned 1.7 million, 2.2 million and 2.4 million U.S. dollars
respectively from DITF '95, DITF '96 and DITF '97.
</P>
<P>
The DITF Steering Committee hoped that export order would be
worth three million dollars this year. 
</P>
