<HEADLINE> 45 Firms in Thailand Obtain International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has the highest
number of the International Standardization Organization (ISO)
14001-certifies companies in Southeast Asia, beating more
competitive countries such as Singapore and Malaysia, according to
Thailand Environment Institute.
</P>
<P>
There are 45 industrial companies in the country out of 2,600
companies worldwide which have obtained the international standard
for environmental management system, the institute was quoted
Sunday by the Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 45 companies have been certified in 1997 by
international bodies.
</P>
<P>
Japan has the highest rate in the world, with over 900
companies awarded the certification. 
</P>
