<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Remarried People in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The number of remarried people
has been on the rise in China in recent years, as remarriage
becomes increasingly understandable and acceptable for the Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey by the State Statistical Bureau, a total
of 862,000 people were registered for remarriage in 1996 in China,
up from 500,000 in 1985 and 788,000 in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Civil affairs departments say that the proportion of the
remarried people among the newly married stood at 3.05 percent in
1985, and it rose to 4.14 percent in 1990 and 4.61 percent in 1996.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, Tianjin and Shanghai, all three with rich culture
and growing economy, the proportion reached 14.67, 10.08, and
13.36 percent, respectively, far above the national average.
</P>
<P>
Remarriage is more consequent in cities, compared with rural
areas. Remarried people accounted for 2.95 percent of the married
in cities and counties, 0.43 percentage points higher than in the
rural areas, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the remarriage of the old people has got more
concern from the society and their legal rights have been better
protected. Statistics show that in 1996, out of 100 married people
above the age of 50, five were the remarried. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
