<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading South African newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Sunday Times
</P>
<P>
-- South Africa's police chief executive officer Meyer Kahn
said at the weekend that he planned to change the the structure
and management of the police service to help fight crime in the
country.
</P>
<P>
-- More than half of South African organizations do not use
any control techniques when conducting electronic commerce,
according to a survey conducted by a local security company.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Independent
</P>
<P>
-- Top leaders of the ruling African National Congress are
meeting in Cape Town to plan its election strategy for 1999,
informed sources revealed at the weekend. 
</P>
