<HEADLINE> Daehlie Wins Men's 50km Cross Country Skiing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian Bjoern Daehlie
proved Sunday in Hakuba that he is the undisputed king of cross
country skiing, winning the men's 50km free style event at the 18th
Olympic Winter Games.
</P>
<P>
This was his third gold in Nagano and eighth overall in his Olympic
career.
</P>
<P>
The victory of the Norwegian team in the 4x10km relay on Wednesday
has made him the most successful Olympian with seven gold medals.
</P>
<P>
Daehlie crossed the finish line in Sunday's race in two hours five
minutes and 8.2 seconds, 8.1 seconds faster than Niklas Jonsson of
Sweden and 53.6 seconds faster than bronze medalist Christian Hoffmann
of Austria.
</P>
<P>
Russian Alexej Prokurorov and Italian Fulvio Valbusa placed fourth
and fifth respectively.
</P>
<P>
Daehlie, winner in the relay and 10km classical skiing, was in te
10th place at the 8.5km mark. Afte 30km, he moved up to the second
place and led the group of 62 with the fastest time after 46.4km.
</P>
<P>
Jonsson, who was in the ninth place after 16.7km and seventh after
29.7km, dramatically quickened his pace in the last 20 kilometers to
challenge Russian Prokurorov, who led at the 16.7km mark. Prokurorov
was 7.3 seconds off Hoffmann's lead at the 29.7km point.
</P>
<P>
Just after Daehlie crossed the finish line, he collapsed to the
snow and he was treated by medics.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think I've ever been so tired in my life," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
