The new investment will be used mainly to upgrade their
services and to move the company's operations to more spacious
premises along the Negombo-Colombo road.
</P>
<P>
The company also plans to expand its services to other cities
across the country by setting up a network of Toyota Lanka
Authorized Service Stations, the general manager said. They hope
to start 30 such stations by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
In the total brand new Japanese vehicles marketed in Sri Lanka,
Toyota has been able to reach the number one position in 1997 in
terms of market share.
</P>
<P>
Abeygoonesekera said out of the 2,939 new vehicles imported
from Japan last year, 950 were Toyotas.
</P>
<P>
Currently 120 to 150 brand new Toyota vehicles are imported
monthly, he added. 
