<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Thailand Keen to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Political stability, timely
government adjustment measures and qualified workforce in Vietnam
have attracted more and more Thai investors, a visiting senior
Thai official said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
When meeting Vietnamese Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign
Minister Nguyen Manh Cam, director of Thai Prime Minister's Office
Somboon Rahong said, "Thai businessmen always consider Vietnam as
a reliable and attractive investment venue," a report of the
Vietnam News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Rahong admitted that the current financial crisis in Southeast
Asia triggered by the sharp fall of Thai baht in August 1997
produced an adverse impact on Thailand's investment in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
But he said he believed that Southeast Asia would continue to
be the most economically dynamic region in the world when the
crisis ends.
</P>
<P>
The minister also expressed the hope that members of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) should strengthen
solidarity to solve the aftermath caused by the crisis, and make
hostile schemes designed by outside forces null and void.
</P>
<P>
He added that Thailand and Vietnam should strive to boost
bilateral ties and set an example for other members of ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Manh Cam said that more than ever before, it is time for
ASEAN countries to enhance mutual cooperation under the principle
that a prosperous nation will add strength to a region, and a
prosperous region will add strength to the world.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Thailand share great potential to accelerate their
comprehensive cooperation not only in the interests of the two
countries but also for the maintenance of regional stability and
development, the deputy prime minister said. 
