<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela Keeps Down Oil Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The price of the Venezuelan
basket of crudes and by-products exported by Venezuela will
continue dropping because of the downward trend of the prices in
the international market.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan Energy and Mines Ministry said that the
country's crude price closed last week at 12.08 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
This figure means an 11 dollar cents over the 11.97 dollars in
which the average price was quoted last Friday 13, although it is
7 cents under the 12.15 dollars of Feb 19.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan crudes basket registered last Wednesday its
lowest average level of the last 20 years, when it closed at 11.70
dollars per barrel and a significant advance in the month of
February when it rose 40 cents the next day.
</P>
<P>
Until February 19, the quotation of the Venezuelan basket
averaged 12.81 dollars per barrel, 1.19 dollars below the average
price of liquidation of 14 dollars per barrel estimated in the
budget of the nation for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Experts in the matter say there is no signal of recovery for
the prices in two or three months, save for some unexpected change
that could make the market react, but in general the prices will
continue in their downward trend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
