<HEADLINE> Development Zones Urged to Emphasize Industrial Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 22 (Xinhua) -- The State Council's
Office of Special Economic Zones recently called on the nation's
development zones to attach greater importance to industrial
restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The call came during a forum on the country's major development
zones held in Langfang Prefecture, north China's Hebei
Province. The office requires development zones to integrate
foreign and domestic funds, while at the same time expanding
exports and maintaining domestic markets.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Director Wan Jifei stressed that development zones must
intensify industrial restructuring efforts to develop hi-tech
industries and those suitable to local conditions, in addition to
altering their modes of economic growth at the earliest possible
date.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that all the 32 major development zones of the
country recorded 10 percent or more increases in industrial output
value, GDP and export volume during 1997. This in turn signaled
the fact that these zones have entered a profitable period. 
