<HEADLINE> Forest Fires Out of Control in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Forest fires in Chile's
northern 10th Region are continuing to sweep everything in their
path, the Regional Office of Emergencies said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The fires have destroyed until now more than 1,600 hectares of
grassland and forests, and the efforts to put them out have been
in vain because of the difficulty in reaching the sites.
</P>
<P>
More fires are occurring in the Putraucao zone, destroying the
green areas with smoke columns darkening the sky in the city of
Puerto Montt.
</P>
<P>
Personnel from the National Forest Corporation, the Army and
Fire Department are working intensely to put out the fires.
