<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Poultry Exports Drop in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's poultry
exports dropped about 31 percent last month, compared to the same
month of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Claudio Martins, director of the Brazilian Poultry Exporters
Association, said Saturday that the country exported 41 million
tons of chickens, against 59 million tons in January of 1997.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the decline to the Asian financial crisis that
caused currency devaluation in several Asian countries against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The country earned 48.53 million dollars from poultry exports
in January, posting a 42 percent drop from that of the same month
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian poultry producers association said that Brazil
increased its sales to Mercosur countries, going from 3,005 tons
in January 1997 to 3,588 tons in last December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
