<HEADLINE> Three People Killed in Bangkok Car Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 22 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and
30 others injured in a car accident in the Capital Saturday, the
Bangkok Post quoted the city's police as saying Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The accident involved six vehicles near a tollway-expressway
exit, police officers said.
</P>
<P>
The collision occurred at mid-day Saturday when an
inter-provincial bus suddenly switched lane as it was approaching
the exit.
</P>
<P>
The bus rammed into the rear of a metered taxi, killing its
driver and a passenger aboard.
</P>
<P>
Police officers said the driver of a car following the bus was
also killed as his car crashed into the bus. 
